<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>HTML Basics</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial;
            background: #f4f6f9;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .container {
            width: 90%;
            margin: auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px #ccc;
        }

        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #2c3e50;
        }

        p {
            text-align: center;
            color: #555;
        }

        .row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .box {
            flex: 1;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        .box h3 {
            background: #3498db;
            color: white;
            padding: 8px;
            margin: -10px -10px 10px -10px;
        }

        .section {
            margin-top: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            background: #2980b9;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .center {
            text-align: right;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>HTML Basics: Tags and Lists</h1>
        <p>Learn about basic HTML tags and how to create lists.</p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="box">
                <h3>HTML Tags</h3>
                HTML tags are building blocks.<br><br>
                &lt;h1&gt; Heading &lt;/h1&gt;<br>
                &lt;p&gt; Paragraph &lt;/p&gt;
            </div>
            <div class="box">
                <h3>Paragraph Tags</h3>
                Use &lt;p&gt; for text.<br><br>
                &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
            </div>
            <div class="box">
                <h3>Lists in HTML</h3>
                Learn about lists:<br><br>
                <a href="lists.html">Ordered Lists</a><br>
                <a href="lists.html">Unordered Lists</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h3>Types of Lists</h3>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="box">
                    <b>Ordered List</b><br><br>
                    <ol>
                        <li>First</li>
                        <li>Second</li>
                        <li>Third</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <div class="box">
                    <b>Unordered List</b><br><br>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Apple</li>
                        <li>Banana</li>
                        <li>Cherry</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="center">
            <a href="Page2.html" class="btn">Next →</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
